article.headline: Massachusetts 32, Villanova 24, OT
article.story: AMHERST, Mass. (AP) -- Liam Coen's 11-yard pass to J.J. Moore in the 4th overtime session helped Massachusetts defeat Villanova, 32-24, on Saturday. The teams were scoreless in the first overtime, but matched TDs in the second extra session. Matt Lawrence got UMass in front on a four-yard run. Chris Whitney equalized for Villanova with a nine-yard touchdown run. The teams matched field goals in the third overtime. Villanova's Joe Marcoux booted his third of the game, hitting from 41-yards. Chris Koepplin got UMass even at 24-24 with a 23-yard boot. UMass went ahead 7-6 in the third quarter on a 13-yard pass from Coen to Ian Jorgensen. Villanova, however, pulled ahead 14-7 in the fourth quarter on an 18-yard pass from Chris Whitney to Matt Sherry. UMass evened the score at 14-all as Coen hit Joe Sanford for a touchdown with 2:09 in regulation to force the overtime thriller. The final outcome lifted UMass to 5-1 overall and 3-0 in the Colonial Athletic Association. Villanova fell to 4-3, 2-2.
